&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discord is committed to inclusion and providing reasonable accommodations during the interview process. &lt;/strong&gt;We want you to feel set up for success, so if you are in need of reasonable accommodations, please let your recruiter know.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please see our Applicant and Candidate Privacy Policy for details regarding Discord’s collection and usage of personal information relating to the application and recruitment process by clicking&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://discord.com/terms/applicant-candidate-privacy-policy&quot;&gt;HERE.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Anthropic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anthropic’s mission is to create reliable, interpretable, and steerable AI systems. We want AI to be safe and beneficial for our users and for society as a whole. Our team is a quickly growing group of committed researchers, engineers, policy experts, and business leaders working together to build beneficial AI systems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;heading&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anthropic&#39;s Infrastructure organization is the engine that powers our mission to develop AI systems that are safe, beneficial, and understandable. Every breakthrough in AI safety research and every interaction users have with Claude depends on the systems we build and operate: massive clusters for training, production infrastructure serving millions of users reliably, and developer platforms that help engineers move fast without breaking things. This isn&#39;t typical infrastructure work. We&#39;re building at the frontier of what&#39;s possible, solving novel scaling challenges that few organizations face with a high degree of security, all in service of ensuring transformative AI benefits humanity. If you&#39;re energized by your technical work directly enabling some of the most important research happening today, Infrastructure at Anthropic is the best place to make a real difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Systems engineering team enables Anthropic to rapidly research and deploy safe frontier models at scale by owning compute uptime and resilience. We build resilience into Anthropic&#39;s infrastructure and support rapid scaling of our clusters with frontier hardware through relentless automation. This allows Anthropic&#39;s research to remain on the frontier of what&#39;s possible and makes research breakthroughs safely and reliably deployable to customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced engineering leader to manage the part of our Systems team that looks after our Kubernetes control plane and custom schedulers. You&#39;ll lead initiatives supporting some of the largest, most sophisticated clusters in the industry used to train, research, and ultimately serve AI models. Your work will be crucial in ensuring Anthropic can continue reliably and safely training frontier models.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;heading&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage a team of engineers building and operating world-class infrastructure at scale&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead build out of industry-leading AI clusters (thousands to hundreds of thousands of machines), partnering closely with cloud service providers on cluster build out and required features&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consult with different stakeholders to deeply understand infrastructure and compute needs, identifying potential solutions to support frontier research and product development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Set technical strategy and oversee development of high-scale, reliable infrastructure systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hire and coach top technical talent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design processes (e.g., postmortem review, incident response, on-call rotations) that help the team operate effectively and never fail the same way twice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drive continuous improvement in system reliability, scalability, and security&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work closely with Research and Product Engineering teams to ensure infrastructure meets their evolving needs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
